## Component Conventions

### UI Primitives (components/UI/)
These are the canonical shared components. ALWAYS prefer these over hand-rolling:

| Component | Use for |
|-----------|---------|
| `Avatar` | User avatars with fallback initials. Sizes: `xs`, `sm`, `md`, `lg`, `xl`, `2xl` |
| `Button` | All buttons |
| `Card` | Card containers |
| `Input` | Form inputs |
| `Skeleton`, `SkeletonPost`, `SkeletonComment`, `SkeletonProfile` | Loading skeletons |
| `Spinner` (from `Loading`) | Spinner indicators. Sizes: `xs`, `sm`, `md`, `lg`, `xl` |
| `LoadingScreen` | Full-page loading |
| `ErrorBoundary` | Error boundaries |
| `Icon`, `ActionIcon` | Icon wrappers |

**Anti-patterns ‚Äî do NOT:**
- Hand-roll avatar circles with fallback icons ‚Äî use `<Avatar>`
- Hand-roll inline spinner divs with `border-top` animation ‚Äî use `<Spinner>` from `UI/Loading`
- Inject `<style jsx>@keyframes spin</style>` ‚Äî `Spinner` component handles this
- Create inline skeleton divs with `className="skeleton-warm"` ‚Äî use `<Skeleton>` or `PostItemSkeleton`
- Import `LoadingSpinner` from `Shared/` ‚Äî use `Spinner` from `UI/Loading`

### Shared Components (components/Shared/)
| Component | Use for |
|-----------|---------|
| `PostSkeleton` | Multi-variant post skeleton (timeline, card, etc.) ‚Äî used in search, category grids |
| `EmptyState` | Empty data states |
| `ErrorState` | Error states with retry |
| `SimpleSearchBar` | Search inputs |

**ALWAYS use `ErrorState` for error displays.** Do not hand-roll inline error divs with motion wrappers.
**ALWAYS use `EmptyState` for empty data.** Do not hand-roll inline empty messages.

### Post skeletons ‚Äî which one to use
- `components/Post/PostItemSkeleton` ‚Äî minimal timeline skeleton for `PostList` (vertical feed). Use in `PostList` and `UserPostsSection`.
- `components/Shared/PostSkeleton` ‚Äî multi-variant skeleton with `variant` prop (`timeline`, `card`, etc.). Use in search results, category grids, and anywhere needing variants.

```js
// CORRECT ‚Äî for the main post list feed
import PostItemSkeleton from '../Post/PostItemSkeleton';

// CORRECT ‚Äî for search results or grids
import PostSkeleton from '../Shared/PostSkeleton';
<PostSkeleton variant="timeline" />
```

### Editor sub-components (components/Editor/)
The publish workflow is split into focused sub-components. Use them independently or compose via `PublishPanel`:

| Component | Responsibility |
|-----------|---------------|
| `CoverImageUploader` | File picker, upload to S3, preview with change/remove overlay |
| `CategorySelector` | Category chip grid, multi-select (max 3), admin create-new inline input |
| `TagInput` | Tag chip input (Enter/comma to add, Backspace to remove, max 5) |

`PublishPanel` (in `Category/`) is the container that composes all three. Props: `title`, `content`, `imageTitle`, `setImageTitle`, `initialCategories`, `initialTags`, `onPublish`, `onCancel`.

### Layout System
Use layout variants from `components/Layout/Layout.js`:
- `HomeLayout` ‚Äî main content + sidebar
- `ArticleLayout` ‚Äî reading layout for posts
- `ProfileLayout` ‚Äî profile pages
- `ReadingLayout` ‚Äî focused reading
- `WriteLayout` ‚Äî editor layout

```js
import { HomeLayout } from '../../components/Layout/Layout';

// Standard page pattern:
<HomeLayout sidebar={<PersonalBlogSidebar />}>
  <YourContent />
</HomeLayout>
```

### Component file structure
```
components/FeatureName/
‚îú‚îÄ‚îÄ MainComponent.js      # Primary exported component
‚îú‚îÄ‚îÄ SubComponent.js        # Internal/child components
‚îî‚îÄ‚îÄ index.js               # Barrel exports (optional)
```

- One component per file
- Export default for the main component
- Use named exports for sub-components in barrel files
- Feature components live in their feature folder, not in `UI/` or `Shared/`
- Local single-use helper components (e.g. `AuthorByline` in `PostDetail`) are fine to keep inline ‚Äî don't extract unless reused elsewhere

