## Styling Rules

### Three-layer system (in priority order)
1. **CSS custom properties** ‚Äî design tokens in `:root` (`var(--text)`, `var(--bg)`, `var(--accent)`, etc.)
2. **Tailwind utility classes** ‚Äî for layout, spacing, responsive
3. **Theme classes** ‚Äî `utils/theme/` for semantic token combos (`themeClasses.text.primary`, `themeClasses.interactive.buttonPrimary`)

### Rules
- Prefer **Tailwind classes** for new components
- Use **CSS variables** for colors: `text-[var(--text)]`, `bg-[var(--bg)]`, `border-[var(--border)]`
- Use **inline `style={{}}`** only when Tailwind can't express it (dynamic values, complex computed styles)
- **Do NOT** mix 3 styling systems in a single component ‚Äî pick the dominant approach
- Use `combineClasses()` from `utils/theme/` to join class strings (replaces `clsx`)
- **Do NOT** hardcode color values like `rgba(26,137,23,...)` ‚Äî use CSS vars or Tailwind theme

### Design tokens (CSS variables)
```
--bg, --bg-surface, --bg-elevated    # Background surfaces
--text, --text-muted, --text-faint   # Text colors
--accent                              # Primary accent (terracotta)
--border, --border-subtle             # Borders
--font-display, --font-body, --font-mono  # Font families
--nav-height                          # Navbar height
```

